    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1446e0a5_893a2a88",
        "filename": "src/gpu/vk/GrVkSampler.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 86,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-31T17:15:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m wondering if for non-external textures if it still makes sense to require a client to pass in the formatFeatures or should we be querying them. I think we should have all the info needed to do the query. For the android external we definitely need it to be passed in since it is queried off of the HardwareBuffer.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 86,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 86,
        "endChar": 69
      },
      "revId": "4e932e9905448c31a3fa2cc033c007681609e25e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e5986140_8ea48d65",
        "filename": "src/gpu/vk/GrVkSampler.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 86,
      "author": {
        "id": 8948
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-31T20:34:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We could use vkGetPhysicalDeviceFormatProperties() here to query format features. Problem is that we don\u0027t know which tiling is used by the source image and features depend on tiling, so then we would need to put tiling flag in GrVkYcbcrConversionInfo.",
      "parentUuid": "1446e0a5_893a2a88",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 86,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 86,
        "endChar": 69
      },
      "revId": "4e932e9905448c31a3fa2cc033c007681609e25e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "489b2ce5_a13b5954",
        "filename": "src/gpu/vk/GrVkSampler.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 86,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-31T20:52:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m fine with leaving this as is for now. FWIW I think all but one of the callers to this (well the callers of the one function that calls this) has access to the tiling. So it is not crazy to think we could pass that into this function.",
      "parentUuid": "e5986140_8ea48d65",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 86,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 86,
        "endChar": 69
      },
      "revId": "4e932e9905448c31a3fa2cc033c007681609e25e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1b21c217_0a1868b4",
        "filename": "src/gpu/vk/GrVkSamplerYcbcrConversion.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 39,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-31T17:15:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not a huge fan of trying to initialize some fields like this and then explicitly setting others (and can lead to compiler bugs like you\u0027re getting). Can we just go ahead a explicitly set everything. Once we are allowed to use named members everywhere I start like this approach more, but till then..",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 38,
        "startChar": 57,
        "endLine": 39,
        "endChar": 68
      },
      "revId": "4e932e9905448c31a3fa2cc033c007681609e25e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "70fe48a7_59fd1e34",
        "filename": "src/gpu/vk/GrVkSamplerYcbcrConversion.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 39,
      "author": {
        "id": 8948
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-31T20:34:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done.\nThe nice thing about initializing the struct like this is that we can be sure that all fields are initialized to 0, even if we don\u0027t set them explicitly.",
      "parentUuid": "1b21c217_0a1868b4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 38,
        "startChar": 57,
        "endLine": 39,
        "endChar": 68
      },
